  "elapsed_s": 100.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the train took off and I was sitting on the top.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And there were other people, peasants, from nearby towns and so on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they had plenty food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They opened up their food, a-- a-- a little towel which was tied in knots, and opened up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And everybody shared food and so on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And in about a day and a half, I had arrived to Budapest, just very close to a sports stadium which was called the [NON-ENGLISH], the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "English translation would be the sports stadium.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] France, which is [NON-ENGLISH] in German, or in English, I suddenly don't have the English name for it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I knew the location.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I knew that what street is it on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So I just started to walk, and walk, and walk, and trying to get back to my own neighborhood and find out what's left of it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The city looked like that there were some scars all over, because the buildings had all kind of signs on the cover of the buildings, on the plaster of the buildings which were gunshot wounds.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many buildings were in despair and burned out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the majority of the city, from what I see from the suburbs as I was moving, was recognizable and well.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As I found out later, there was not one single bridge on the Danube which was intact.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you couldn't cross from one side of the city to the other, just like here in the Potomac River dividing us from Washington DC to Virginia, and all these wonderful bridges, that would be none of them existing.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was some six, seven bridges of Budapest, which was all blown up by the Germans as they retreated to slow down the Russian movement.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
